    /// - `<d>` — Is the number of the SIMD&FP destination register, in the "Rd" field.
    /// - `<n>` — Is the number of the first SIMD&FP source register, encoded in the "Rn" field.
    /// - `<Vd>` — Is the name of the SIMD&FP destination register, encoded in the "Rd" field.
    /// - `<T>` — Is an arrangement specifier, 0000 → x, 0001 → 0, 0001 → 1, 001x → 0, 001x → 1, 01xx → 0, 01xx → 1, 1xxx → 0, 1xxx → 1
    /// - `<Vn>` — Is the name of the SIMD&FP source register, encoded in the "Rn" field.
    /// - `<shift>` — For the scalar variant: is the right shift amount, in the range 1 to 64, 0xxx → RESERVED, 1xxx → (128-UInt(immh:immb))
    /// - `<shift>` — For the vector variant: is the right shift amount, in the range 1 to the element width in bits, 0000 → SEE Advanced SIMD modified immediate, 0001 → (16-UInt(immh:immb)), 001x → (32-UInt(immh:immb)), 01xx → (64-UInt(immh:immb)), 1xxx → (128-UInt(immh:immb))
